				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Epic 1.5 - The Code of Silence Experience, Part 3<a name="68294"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 27 04 12:44 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Grats on the progress you guys are making.  I would offer this advice on DN2:  coordination will let you get past the liches, and then Vasthon.  I heard from a bard friend that DN2 is like DN1, in that the event timer is short to get the draco popped, but you have some time after that, say 30 minutes. This allows you to take a shot at him when Vasthon dies, just keep a rogue and necro alive for recovery.  
<br />

<br />
This way, you have time to get everyone ready for the fight with the draco.  Then take a real shot at him.  What I found was that people get fairly spread out while killing liches, so that when Draco popped, we weren't in position, and lost most of the 12 people that died in the first 15 seconds.  After that we lost no one.  
<br />

<br />
As for dragging your guild around for help, the swamp dragon is doable with 1+ group.  We did it single group, and it was close, but an EP guild could do it with 10 people easy.  You will need 3 groups for other 2 dragons though.
<br />

<br />
Keep up the progress, the new Epics are very cool.  They are a status symbol; not of being a raider or being hard core, but of having lots of friends or guildies that help each other out.  A bard with an Epic means he is part of a good sized community.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
