				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Epic 1.5 - The Code of Silence Experience, Part 3<a name="68298"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 27 04 1:11 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>We tried swamp dragon Monday with our normal group - warrior, druid, shaman, mage, wizard, and me along with a 2-boxed bard and cleric -- and we got whipped.  Basically, the DoT healing just sucked up all the mana for us.  I won't risk wasting people's time on him without 12-15 people minimum and probably 3 groups.
<br />

<br />
Let me ask you this -- is there any non-God named mob in the elemental planes that you would compare to the Dracoliche for difficulty?  Is he Krziik the Mighty?  Qavonis Firetail?  Peregrin Rockskull?  Can you make a comparison on difficulty?  It would be a great help to have something to guage it by.
<br />

<br />
Thanks, Kanarian.</span></td>
