			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Epic 1.5 - The Code of Silence Experience, Part 3<a name="68319"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 27 04 3:28 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I can't really think of any EP mobs that have the unique characteristics of thie fight.  Best reference would be the Plains dragon plus the Forest Dragon, with fewer HP.  It has AE ramp, and an AE spell that can kill off your DPS.  The fight is like Trakanon, in that if you are going to win, it will be in the first 4 minutes or so.  After that, healers can't keep up the healing.  So have damage classes start burning sooner than on most mobs.  
<br />

<br />
The max hit isn't too bad, maybe 1200ish, and it is important to let most healers use group and AE heals, along with spams.  If you keep your tank and DPS up for 2 to 3 minutes, you win.  
<br />

<br />
Also remember that if you can run a coordinated raid, you will have a bit of time to rez up and med if you do not kill the last skelly lich.  you can have a bard mez lock its pet, the lich wont attack until it is damaged a bit.  So best bet, be ready to burn down Vasthon, then the draco, keep DPS up for the fight or his AE's will outdamage your healer mana pools.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
